.TH "rfc4543_gcm_esp_setkey" 9 "rfc4543_gcm_esp_setkey" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rfc4543_gcm_esp_setkey \- setkey operation for RFC4543 variant of GCM/GMAC. cipher: AEAD structure key: Key followed by 4 bytes of salt keylen: Length of key plus salt, in bytes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rfc4543_gcm_esp_setkey
.BI "(struct crypto_aead *cipher "  ","
.BI "const u8 *key "  ","
.BI "unsigned int keylen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cipher" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "key" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "keylen" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Extracts salt from key and stores it to be prepended to IV on each request.
Digest is always 16 bytes
.SH "RETURN"
Value from generic gcm setkey.
